{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566776","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566776"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:48:06+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:48:06+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18878"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18878","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18878"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.06,0.86,0.06,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11611"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80154"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11611","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11611"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18878"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65431"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"5512"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11323"},{"type":"tags","id":"11332"},{"type":"tags","id":"11333"},{"type":"tags","id":"11374"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27321"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27389"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80154","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80154"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA medical student has just completed their first clinical rotation. During a debrief session, their supervisor introduces the concept of structured reflection using established frameworks. The supervisor emphasises the importance of moving beyond simple description of events to deeper analysis.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary purpose of reflective practice?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["To identify and highlight mistakes in others\u0027 clinical practices","To focus on improving technical skills by practicing repeatedly","To critically evaluate personal experiences and identify areas for improvement","To ensure compliance with institutional policies and guidelines","To memorise and follow standard treatment protocols"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe primary purpose of reflective practice is to \u003Cstrong\u003Ecritically evaluate personal experiences and identify areas for improvement\u003C/strong\u003E. This involves systematic analysis of experiences using structured frameworks to generate meaningful insights that drive professional development.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETo identify and highlight mistakes in others\u0027 clinical practices\u003C/strong\u003E - Reflection focuses on self-evaluation rather than critiquing others\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETo focus on improving technical skills by practicing repeatedly\u003C/strong\u003E - While skill development is important, reflection involves deeper analysis of experiences beyond repetitive practice\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETo ensure compliance with institutional policies and guidelines\u003C/strong\u003E - Reflection goes beyond simply following rules to understanding and improving practice\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETo memorise and follow standard treatment protocols\u003C/strong\u003E - Reflection involves critical thinking rather than rote memorisation\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EEffective reflection requires moving beyond simple description to analyse experiences systematically, consider multiple perspectives, and develop specific plans for improvement. This process helps practitioners grow professionally and enhance their clinical practice.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Reflective practice is a structured approach to critically examine experiences and identify areas for professional growth.","Effective reflection involves systematic analysis rather than simple description of events.","The goal of reflection is to drive meaningful changes in professional practice through self-evaluation."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx.","Koshy K, Limb C, Gundogan B, Whitehurst K, Jafree DJ. Reflective practice in health care and how to reflect effectively. Int J Surg Oncol (N Y). 2017 Jul;2(6):e20. Available at: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC5673148/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65431"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18878"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65431","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65431"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-17T20:39:12+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-17T20:40:08+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11611"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80154"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attri